at0000.1.description: The reason for initiation of any healthcare encounter or contact by the individual who is the subject of care.

at0004.1.description: Identification of the clinical or social problem motivating the subject of care to seeking healthcare.
at0004.1.comment: Coding of the 'Presenting problem' with a terminology is desirable, where possible. Clinical or social reasons for seeking healthcare can include health issues, symptoms or physical signs. Examples: health issues - desire to quit smoking, domestic violence; symptoms - abdominal pain, shortness of breath; physical signs - an altered conscious state. 'Chief complaint' may be used as a valid synonym for 'Presenting problem' in templates.
